
### Potato salad


### Sweet Home Cafe p.26

* 2 lb Yukon Gold
* 3 t kosher salt
* 1/4 C onion
* 1/4 C cider vinegar
* 2 T sugar
* 3/4 C mayo

* 3 T yellow mustard
* 1/4 C sweet pickle relish
* 1/2 cup celery, diced
* 1/4 parsley, chopped
* 1/4 C scallions, white and light green, thinly sliced
* pepper to taste

* Put potatoes and 2 T salt into a large pot and cover with cold water
* Boil and cook until tender (~25m)
* Drain and let cool to room temperature
* (rinse onions in a small strainer)
* combine vinegar, sugar, remaining 1 T salt and whisk until dissolved
* add mayo, mustard, relish; whisk until well-blended
* add potatoes, celery, onion, parsley, scallion to mayo; gently mix
* refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving
* once chilled, salt and pepper to taste






### Perini p. 58

* 2 lb red or white boiling potatoes
* 1/4 C olive oil
* 2 T vinegar
* 1 t prepared mustard
* 2 green onions, finely sliced
* 1 T chopped parsley
* 1/2 t salt
* 1/2 t pepper

* boil potatoes about 20 minutes
* slice and toss with remaining ingredients
